title: [Nanetta's Cafe, Wine Cellar]
description: Though dimly lit and moderately chilly, this storage cellar is free of dust and appears well maintained.  A sturdy modwir table is covered with a crisp white linen tablecloth.  Beside the table, a single burning wall sconce illuminates a neatly carved sign.  Filling the remainder of the space, a large solid oak rack holds row upon row of hand labeled wines.
room.location: Grawood Farmstead outside of River's Rest
